data.meta_desc: Perhaps the most-terrifying space photograph around. Astronaut Bruce McCandless II floats untethered away from the safety of the space shuttle with nothing but his Manned Maneuvering Unit keeping him alive. The first person in history to do so. "My wife was at mission control and there was quite a bit of apprehension" he recalled in 2015 to the Guardian. "I wanted to say something similar to Neil Armstrong when he landed on the moon so I said It may have been a small step for Neil but its a heck of a big leap for me That loosened the tension a bit. Memes.
